Q : What is Stored Procedure ?
Ans : A stored procedure is group of T-SQL (Transact SQL) statements. If you have a situation, where you write the same query over and over again, you can save that specific query as a stored procedure and call it just by it's name.


//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Q : How to Create a Stored Procedure without Parameter ?
Ans : Consider a Table 

![alt text](./Images/image_10.png)

-> Creating a Stored Procedure Without Paramaeters.

CREATE PROCEDURE spGetEmployees
AS 
BEGIN
    SELECT Name , Gender FROM tblEmployee
END

-> To Execute
EXEC spGetEmployees

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Q : How to Create a Stored Procedure with Parameter ?
Ans : 
-> Creating a Stored Procedure With Parameters.

CREATE PROCEDURE spGetEmployeeByGenderAndDepartment
@Gender nvarchar(50),
@DepartmentId int

AS
BEGIN
    SELECT Name, Gender FROM tblEmployee WHERE Gender = @Gender AND DepartmentId = @DepartmentId
END

-> How To Exceute 
EXECUTE spGetEmployeesByGenderAndDepartment 'Male', 1

Note : The Order Should be same as How Parameters are defined.

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

-> To change the stored procedure, use ALTER PROCEDURE statement:

Alter Procedure spGetEmployeesByGenderAndDepartment 
@Gender nvarchar(50),
@DepartmentId int
as
Begin
  Select Name, Gender from tblEmployee Where Gender = @Gender and DepartmentId = @DepartmentId order by Name
End

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

-> To View The Text Of Strored PRocedure 

sp_helptext 'SPName'
This Will Display the Text of Stored Procdure


//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

-> Excrypt the Text OF SP

Alter Procedure spGetEmployeesByGenderAndDepartment 
@Gender nvarchar(50),
@DepartmentId int
WITH ENCRYPTION
as
Begin
  Select Name, Gender from tblEmployee Where Gender = @Gender and DepartmentId = @DepartmentId
End

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

-> Delete Stroed PRocedure
DROP PROC 'SPName' or DROP PROCEDURE 'SPName'
